OL,3,CReports over hitting and smacking of
OL,4,Cchildren triple in a year, NSPCC says
OL,6,FConcerns raised to the NSPCC about
OL,7,Fchildren being hit, smacked and shaken
OL,8,Fhave more than tripled in a year, the
OL,9,Fcharity said, prompting a renewed call
OL,10,Ffor a change in the law.
OL,12,FWhile there were 447 child welfare
OL,13,Fcontacts to the helpline where
OL,14,Fphysical punishment was mentioned in
OL,15,Fthe year to March 2023, this jumped to
OL,16,F1,451 in the 12 months to March this
OL,17,Fyear.
